1) 80C
Maximum limit: ₹1.5 lakh per year
Covers investments and expenses like:
PPF (Public Provident Fund)
EPF
Life Insurance Premium
ELSS mutual funds
Home loan principal repayment
Tuition fees for children
Example:
If your income is ₹6,00,000 and you invest ₹1,50,000 in 80C,
Taxable income = ₹6,00,000 – ₹1,50,000 = ₹4,50,000

2) 80D
Deduction for health insurance premium
₹25,000 for self/family
Additional ₹25,000 (or ₹50,000 if parents are senior citizens)
Helps reduce tax if you pay medical insurance.

3) HRA (House Rent Allowance)
If you are a salaried employee and live in a rented house:
HRA exemption depends on:
Actual HRA received
Rent paid – 10% of salary
40% (non-metro) or 50% (metro) of salary
The lowest of the above is allowed as deduction.
